entries.d:
a. Not absorbable; specifically (Physiol.), not capable
of absorption; unable to pass by osmosis into the circulating blood;
as, the unabsorbable portion of food.

a. Not capable of being brought into harmony;
irreconcilable.
a. Incapable of being atoned for; inexpiable.

v. t. To free from a charge or load; to unload.
v. t. To free from an accusation; to make no charge against;
to acquit.

n. The burden of a song; the chorus; the refrain.
n. Accompanying strain; subordinate and underlying meaning;
accompaniment; undertone.

a. Driven from a house; deprived of shelter.
a. Not provided with a house or shelter; houseless;
homeless.

a. Having no meaning or signification; as, unmeaning words.
a. Not indicating intelligence or sense; senseless;
expressionless; as, an unmeaning face.

a. Having no moral perception, quality, or relation;
involving no idea of morality; -- distinguished from both moral and
immoral.
